<refentry xml:id="vtiful-kernel-excel.getDefinedNames" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getDefinedNames</refname>
  <refpurpose>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel getDefinedNames</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <modifier>public</modifier> <type>array</type><methodname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getDefinedNames</methodname>
   <void/>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <simpara>Returns the defined names (named ranges) declared in the workbook currently open for reading.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  &no.function.parameters;
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <simpara>An array of defined names, each entry an associative array with the keys <literal>name</literal>, <literal>formula</literal>, <literal>scope</literal> (the sheet name for a sheet-scoped name, &null; for a workbook-scoped name) and <literal>hidden</literal>. Returns &null; when no workbook is open for reading.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>
